&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5 – Paediatric Nurse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Childrens’ Emergency Department&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for dynamic, hard working paediatric nurses who are enthusiastic and keen to develop their clinical, managerial and teaching skills. You will be expected to deliver high quality and timely care to children and their families and support other members of the team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Although experience would be desirable we are prepared to recruit newly qualified paediatric nurses who demonstrate a keen desire to work within the field of paediatric emergency medicine. Any successful applicant would have a period of supernumery status, we operate a buddy support network and have a robust induction programme.We are a busy unit treating a wide range of illness and injury in children under 16 years of age.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We, in return are committed to your development through a robust appraisal system and the opportunity to rotate to the other paediatric emergency areas within the Trust. We can also help you develop into a paediatric ENP or ACP.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a large Foundation Teaching Trust with a commitment to patient care and staff development. So if you fancy a demanding, but rewarding, position with job security apply now!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information or an informal visit please contact: - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Maxine Tomlinson Lead Nurse, Children’s Emergency Department on 0121 424 0481 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;OR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Jessica Causer Paediatric Sister, Children’s Emergency Department on 0121 424 0481&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date 10th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be held on 23&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;rd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;At University Hospitals Birmingham we support flexible working and welcome applications from nurses seeking flexible working opportunities and family friendly working hours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
